_2\"><div class=\"top-container\"><div class=\"top-g\" id=\"careful_topg_3\"><div class=\"webtop\"><span class=\"idm\" id=\"careful_idm_2\">careful with money</span> </div></div></div><ol class=\"sense_single\" htag=\"ol\"><li class=\"sense\" htag=\"li\" id=\"careful_sng_6\" hclass=\"sense\"><span class=\"sensetop\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"sensetop\"><span class=\"def\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"def\">not spending money on things that are unimportant</span></span><ul class=\"examples\" hclass=\"examples\" htag=\"ul\"><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"x\">His mother had always been careful with money.</span></li></ul>      </li></ol></span> <span class=\"idm-g\" id=\"careful_idmg_1\" sk=\"youcantbetoocareful\"><div class=\"top-container\"><div class=\"top-g\" id=\"careful_topg_2\"><div class=\"webtop\"><span class=\"idm\" id=\"careful_idm_1\">you can’t be too careful</span> </div></div></div><ol class=\"sense_single\" htag=\"ol\"><li class=\"sense\" htag=\"li\" id=\"careful_sng_5\" hclass=\"sense\"><span class=\"sensetop\" hclass=\"sensetop\" htag=\"span\"><span class=\"def\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"def\">used to warn somebody that they should take care to avoid danger or problems</span></span><ul class=\"examples\" hclass=\"examples\" htag=\"ul\"><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"x\">Don't stay out in the sun for too long—you can't be too careful.</span></li></ul>      </li></ol></span></div><span class=\"dictlink-g\"><span class=\"dictlink\">See <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/american_english/careful\" title=\" definition in American English\n \"><span class=\"xh\">careful</span></a> in the Oxford Advanced American Dictionary</span><span class=\"dictlink\">See <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/academic/careful\" title=\" definition in Academic English\n \"><span class=\"xh\">careful</span></a> in the Oxford Learner's Dictionary of Academic English</span></span><div c